FAQs

What are the admission requirements for Tbilisi State Medical University? Admission requirements typically include a high school diploma, proficiency in English, and passing an entrance exam or interview. Specific requirements may vary, so it's best to check the university's official website for details.

Is the degree from TSMU recognized internationally? Yes, degrees from Tbilisi State Medical University are recognized internationally. TSMU graduates are eligible to practice medicine in many countries, subject to passing the required licensing exams.

What languages are courses taught in at TSMU? Courses at TSMU are primarily taught in English and Georgian. International students usually enroll in the English-language programs.

Does TSMU offer scholarships for international students? TSMU offers various scholarships and financial aid options for international students. Information about available scholarships can be found on the university's website.

What is the cost of living in Tbilisi for students? The cost of living in Tbilisi is relatively affordable. On average, students can expect to spend around $400 to $600 per month on accommodation, food, transportation, and other expenses.
